orting Young Actress|Best Performance in a Feature Film \u2013 Supporting Young Actress]]\n|''Carriers''\n|{{nom}}\n!align=center|<ref name=\"31st Young Artist Award\"/>\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2011\n|[[18th Screen Actors Guild Awards|Screen Actors Guild]]\n|[[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series|Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series]]\n|''Mad Men''\n|{{nom}}\n!align=center|<ref name=SAG/>\n|-\n|Young Artist Awards\n|[[32nd Young Artist Awards#Best Performance in a Feature Film - Leading Young Actress Ten and Under|Best Performance in a Feature Film \u2013 Leading Young Actress Ten and Under]]\n|''Cats & Dogs: The Revenge of Kitty Galore''\n|{{nom}}\n!align=center|<ref name=\"32nd Young Artist Award\">{{Citation|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms32.html |title=32nd Annual Young Artist Awards |accessdate=May 1, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130808150433/http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms32.html |archivedate=August 8, 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n|Young Artist Awards\n|[[32nd Young Artist Awards#Best Performance in a TV Series (Comedy or Drama) - Supporting Young Actress|Best Performance in a TV Series (Comedy or Drama) \u2013 Supporting Young Actress]]\n|rowspan=2|''Mad Men''\n|{{nom}}\n!align=center|<ref name=\"32nd Young Artist Award\"/>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2012\n|[[Young Hollywood Awards]]\n|Scene Stealer Female\n|{{won}}\n!align=center|<ref>{{cite web|author1=Jon Weisman|title=CW to Broadcast Young Hollywood Awards Aug. 1|url=https://variety.com/2013/film/awards/cw-to-broadcast-young-hollywood-awards-aug-1-1200477194/|publisher=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=July 28, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n|Young Artist Awards\n|[[33rd Young Artist Awards#Best Performance in a TV Movie, Miniseries or Special|Best Performance in a TV Movie, Miniseries or Special \u2013 Leading Young Actress]]\n|''Smooch''\n|{{nom}}\n!align=center|<ref name=\"Young Artist Awards 1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/presidents.html|title=Young Artist Awards \u2013 President's Message|accessdate=March 31, 2011|work=YoungArtistAwards.org}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=4|2013\n|[[19th Screen Actors Guild Awards|Screen Actors Guild]]\n|[[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series|Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series]]\n|''Mad Men''\n|{{nom}}\n!align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118063503/\n|title= 'Lincoln,' 'Silver Linings' top SAG film noms|date= December 12, 2012|work=Variety.com |accessdate=December 13, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|Young Artist Awards\n|[[34th Young Artist Awards#Best Performance in a Voice-Over Role (Television) - Young Actress|Best Performance in a Voice-Over Role (Television) \u2013 Young Actress]]\n|''The Legend of Korra''\n|{{nom}}\n!align=center|<ref name=\"Young Artist Awards 3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms34.html |title=34th Annual Young Artist Awards |accessdate=January 3, 2013 |work=YoungArtistAwards.org |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6FaZ1wnUQ?url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms34.html |archivedate=April 2, 2013 |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n|Young Artist Awards\n|[[34th Young Artist Awards#Best Performance in a TV Series - Recurring Young Actress|Best Performance in a TV Series \u2013 Recurring Young Actress]]\n|rowspan=2|''Mad Men''\n|{{won}}\n!align=center|<ref name=\"Young Artist Awards 3\"/>\n|-\n|[[Women in Film Crystal + Lucy Awards]]\n|Lucy Award\n|{{won}}\n!align=center|<ref>{{cite web|title=Crystal + Lucy Awards 2013|url=http://www.wif.org/crystal-lucy2013|publisher=Women in Film Los Angeles|date=April 29, 2013|access-date=March 27, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140809135934/http://www.wif.org/crystal-lucy2013|archive-date=August 9, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|2014\n|[[2014 Young Hollywood Awards|Young Hollywood Awards]]\n|You're So Fancy\n|\n|{{nom}}\n!align=center|<ref name=Guardian>{{cite web|author1=Douglas Cobb|title=2014 Young Hollywood Awards Show Nominees|url=http://guardianlv.com/2014/07/2014-young-hollywood-awards-show-nominees-preview/|publisher=Guardian Liberty Voice|accessdate=July 28, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2019\n|[[2019 MTV Movie & TV Awards]]\n|Best Performance in a Show\n| ''Chilling Adventures of Sabrina''\n| {{nom}}\n!\n|-\n|[[45th Saturn Awards|Saturn Awards]]\n|Best Actress in a Streaming Presentation \n| ''Chilling Adventures of Sabrina''\n|{{Nominated}}\n!align=center|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mancuso |first1=Vinnie |title='Avengers: Endgame', 'Game of Thrones' Lead the 2019 Saturn Awards Nominations |url=http://collider.com/saturn-awards-nominations-2019/ |website=Collider |accessdate=16 July 2019 |date=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2019 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n|Choice Sci-Fi/Fantasy TV Actress\n| ''Chilling Adventures of Sabrina''\n|{{nom}}\n!align=center|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Moreau |first1=Jordan |title=\u2018Avengers: Endgame,\u2019 \u2018Riverdale,\u2019 \u2018Aladdin\u2019 Top 2019 Teen Choice Award Nominations |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/teen-choice-awards-nominations-avengers-endgame-riverdale-1203247410/ |website=Variety |accessdate=19 July 2019 |language=en |date=19 June 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Kiernan Shipka}}\n* {{IMDb name|2215143}}\n\n{{ScreenActorsGuildAwards EnsembleTVDrama 2000\u20132009}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shipka, Kiernan}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Chicago]]\n[[Category:American child actresses]]\n[[Category:American child models]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actress}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Kiernan Shipka\n| image              = Kiernan Shipka at PaleyFest 2014 HQ.jpg\n| caption            = Shipka  at [[Paley Center for Media|PaleyFest 2014]]\n| birth_name         = Kiernan Brennan Shipka\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1999|11|10}}\n| birth_place        = [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], U.S.\n| nationality        = American\n| occupation         = Actress\n| yearsactive        = 2006\u2013present\n}}\n'''Kiernan Brennan Shipka''' (born November 10, 1999) is an American actress best known for her role as [[List of Mad Men characters#Sally Draper|Sally Draper]] in the [[AMC (TV channel)|AMC]] drama series ''[[Mad Men]]'' and as [[Sabrina Spellman]] in the [[Netflix]] series ''[[Chilling Adventures of Sabrina (TV series)|Chilling Adventures of Sabrina]]''. She also appeared as [[B. D. Hyman]] in the [[FX (TV channel)|FX]] series ''[[Feud: Bette and Joan]]'' and voiced Jinora in ''[[The Legend of Korra]]''.<ref name=\"deadline\">{{cite web |last= Petski |first= Denise |title= Kiernan Shipka To Star In Netflix's Sabrina The Teenage Witch Series |url= http://deadline.com/2018/01/kiernan-shipka-star-netflix-sabrina-the-teenage-witch-series-1202236650/ |website= Deadline |accessdate= January 5, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nShipka has also starred in numerous films, including ''[[Carriers (film)|Carriers]]'' (2009), ''[[Flowers in the Attic (2014 film)|Flowers in the Attic]]'' (2014), ''[[The Blackcoat's Daughter]]'' (2015), and ''[[The Silence (2019 film)|The Silence]]'' (2019).\n\n==Early life==\nShipka was born in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], to John Young Shipka, a real estate developer, and Erin Ann Brennan.<ref name=MadTween/><ref name=Kiddieland/><ref>{{cite web |date= December 23, 1995 |title=Erin Brennan, John Shipka|work=articles.chicagotribune.com |url= http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1995-12-23/entertainment/9512230088_1_chicago-erin-brennan-university-of-notre-dame |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20130319105521/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1995-12-23/entertainment/9512230088_1_chicago-erin-brennan-university-of-notre-dame | archive-date= 2013-03-19 |accessdate= November 24, 2019 }}</ref> Shipka has been taking [[ballroom dancing]] classes since the age of five.<ref>{{cite news|last=Chang|first=Bee-Shyuan|title=Growth Spurts Considered: Kiernan Shipka of 'Mad Men' \u2014 What I Wore|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/25/fashion/kiernan-shipka-of-mad-men.html|accessdate=September 21, 2012|newspaper=The New York Times|date=March 23, 2012}}</ref> Her family relocated to [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] when she was six to support her acting career.<ref name=Kiddieland/>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Kiernan Shipka (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|upright|Shipka at the 2010 [[Screen Actors Guild Awards]]]]\nShipka made her television debut at five months of age as a baby on the hospital drama, ''[[ER (TV series)|ER]]''.<ref name=\"dazeddigital\" /> She also began doing commercial-print modeling when she was a baby.<ref name=MadTween>{{cite web |url= http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2010-08-13/features/ct-ae-0815-kiernan-shipka-20100813_1_sally-draper-mad-men-mad-men-s |title='Mad' tween takes drama in stride|first= Maureen|last= Ryan|work=articles.chicagotribune.com |date= August 13, 2012|accessdate=March 24, 2012 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130319105525/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2010-08-13/features/ct-ae-0815-kiernan-shipka-20100813_1_sally-draper-mad-men-mad-men-s | archive-date = March 19, 2013 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nAfter some small television roles, her first major role was as Sally Draper, the daughter of main character [[Don Draper]], on the 2007-2015 TV series ''Mad Men''. She won the role after two auditions.<ref name = NYT032615>{{cite news |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/29/fashion/growing-up-on-mad-men-a-conversation-with-matthew-weiner-and-kiernan-shipka.html |title=Growing Up on 'Mad Men': A Conversation With Matthew Weiner and Kiernan Shipka|first= Philip|last= Galanes|work=[[The New York Times]] |date=March 26, 2015|publisher=[[New York Times Company|NYTC]] |location=[[New York, NY|New York]] |issn=0362-4331 |accessdate=March 28, 2015}}</ref> She was a recurring guest star for the show's first three seasons, then became a series regular in [[Mad Men (season 4)|season four]].<ref name=Kiddieland>{{cite web |url= http://www.suntimes.com/entertainment/television/11428482-421/chicago-girl-goes-from-kiddieland-to-sterling-cooper.html |title=Chicago girl goes from Kiddieland to Sterling Cooper|first= Lori|last= Rackl|work= [[Chicago Sun Times]]|date= March 23, 2012|accessdate=March 24, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130319105537/http://www.suntimes.com/entertainment/television/11428482-421/chicago-girl-goes-from-kiddieland-to-sterling-cooper.html|archive-date=March 19, 2013}}</ref>\n\nAs part of ''Mad Men''<nowiki>'</nowiki>s ensemble cast, she won the [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series]] in 2008 and 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory?id=9647207 |title=Stars of TV and Film Mingle at SAG Awards \u2013 ABC News |publisher=abcnews.go.com |accessdate= March 2, 2010|date= January 24, 2010|author= Anthony McCartney}}</ref>\n\nShipka received praise for her performance on ''Mad Men''. In 2010, ''[[Austin American-Statesman]]'' critic Dale Roe named her as his dream nominee for the [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actress in a Drama Series]], writing, \"This 10-year-old actress was so affecting as troubled Sally Draper last season that it seems odd that she's only just been upgraded to series regular. If Shipka's upcoming ''Mad Men'' work\u2014struggling with the broken marriage of her parents and entering preteendom in the tumultuous 1960s\u2014remains as amazing as it was in [[Mad Men (season 3)|season three]], this is a ballot wish that could come true next year.\"<ref name=\"roe\">Dale Roe. \"Devoted TV watchers name their dream Emmy winners\", ''Austin American-Statesman'', July 4, 2010, page H-1.</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Shipka was named one of \"The 25 Most Influential Teens of 2014\" by [[Time Magazine|''Time'' magazine]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/3486048/most-influential-teens-2014/|title=The 25 Most Influential Teens of 2014|accessdate=May 5, 2015|date=October 13, 2014|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|publisher=Time Inc.}}</ref> That same year, [[IndieWire]] included her in their list of \"20 Actors To Watch That Are Under 20\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Staff|first1=The Playlist|title=On The Rise: 20 Actors To Watch That Are Under 20|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2014/09/on-the-rise-20-actors-to-watch-that-are-under-20-272876/|website=Indiewire|accessdate=February 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\nShipka starred in the 2014 [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] movie ''[[Flowers in the Attic (2014 film)|Flowers in the Attic]]'', and co-starred (with [[Emma Roberts]]) in the 2015 [[Oz Perkins]] horror film ''[[The Blackcoat's Daughter]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bloody-disgusting.com/news/3356186/emma-roberts-leaves-trail-blood-february/|title=Trail of Blood In 'February'|accessdate=May 5, 2015|date=October 13, 2014|work=[[Bloody Disgusting]]|publisher=BD}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, she portrayed [[B.D. Hyman]], daughter of [[Bette Davis]], in the FX television series ''[[Feud (TV series)|Feud: Bette and Joan]]''.\n\nIn January 2018, it was announced that Shipka would be starring as [[Sabrina Spellman]] in [[Netflix]]'s ''[[Chilling Adventures of Sabrina (TV series)|Chilling Adventures of Sabrina]]'' series based on the [[Chilling Adventures of Sabrina|comic series of the same name]].<ref name=\"deadline\" /> The first season was released by [[Netflix]] on October 26, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/10/26/netflixs-chilling-adventures-of-sabrina-season-1-review |title= Netflix's Chilling Adventures of Sabrina: Season 1 Review |last= Lutes |first= Alicia |work= [[IGN]] |date= October 26, 2018 |accessdate= October 27, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nShipka co-starred in a 2019 [[Christmas film|Christmas]] [[romantic comedy]] film directed by [[Luke Snellin]], ''[[Let It Snow (2019 film)|Let It Snow]]'', based on the [[Let It Snow: Three Holiday Romances|novel of the same name]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/kiernan-shipka-isabela-moner-shameik-moore-odeya-rush-netflix-film-let-it-snow-1202536870/|title=Kiernan Shipka, Isabela Moner, Shameik Moore, Odeya Rush & More To Star In Netflix YA Film 'Let It Snow'|work=Deadline Hollywood |first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=December 17, 2018}}</ref> Shooting began in February 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.backstage.com/resources/detail/productionlisting/let-it-snow-86864/|title=Let It Snow|website=Backstage|access-date=March 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\nShipka next played a deaf teenager opposite [[Stanley Tucci]] in [[John R. Leonetti]]'s [[horror film]] ''[[The Silence (2019 film)|The Silence]]'', based on the 2015 horror novel of the same name by [[Tim Lebbon]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Lodderhose|first=Diana|url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/kiernan-shipka-john-leonetti-horror-the-silence-constantin-film-resident-evil-emjag-cannes-mister-smith-entertainment-1202091581/|title=Kiernan Shipka To Star In John Leonetti's 'The Silence' From Constantin Film & EMJAG \u2013 Cannes|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=May 12, 2017}}</ref> Netflix released ''The Silence'' on April 10, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2019/03/19/netflix-april-highlights-include-kevin-hart-special-and-sabrina/3203491002/|title=New on Netflix in April 2019: Kevin Hart, 'Sabrina' and more Noah Centineo|website=[[USA Today]]|first=Bill|last=Keveney|date=March 19, 2019}}</ref> Shipka learned [[American Sign Language]] for the role. Leonetti praised her performance saying \"She's acting alongside Stanley Tucci, and believe me, she's more than holding her own. It's been spellbinding watching her.\"<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Roxborough |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/john-leonettis-horror-movie-silence-deafness-is-adding-extra-scares-afm-2017-1054521|title=How Deafness Is Adding Extra Scares to John Leonetti's Horror Movie 'The Silence'|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=November 3, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nShipka names [[Grace Kelly]] and [[Audrey Hepburn]] as fashion influences.<ref name=VanityFair>\"It's Evening in America\". ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]''. May 2012. Page 159.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2014/04/kiernan-shipka-mad-men|title=What Kiernan Shipka Thinks of Mad Men Now That She's Finally Allowed to Watch It|website=Vanity Fair}}</ref><ref name=\"dazeddigital\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dazeddigital.com/artsandculture/article/29598/1/kiernan-shipka-wide-awake-in-dreamland|title=Kiernan Shipka: wide awake in dreamland|accessdate=November 13, 2016|date=February 9, 2016|work=[[Dazed]]|publisher=Dazed}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n|2007\n|''Dimension''\n|Molly\n|\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Lower Learning]]''\n|Sarah\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=4|2009\n|''{{sortname|A|Rag Doll Story|nolink=1}}''\n|Girl\n|Short film\n|-\n|''[[Land of the Lost (film)|Land of the Lost]]''\n|Tar Pits Kid\n|Uncredited\n|-\n|''[[Carriers (film)|Carriers]]''\n|Jodie\n|\n|-\n|''[[House Broken (2009 film)|House Broken]]''\n|Tammy Tawber\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2010\n|''[[Cats & Dogs: The Revenge of Kitty Galore]]''\n|Little Girl at playground\n|\n|-\n|''{{sortname|The|Ryan and Randi Show|nolink=1}}''\n|Lala La Lala\n|Short film\n|-\n|''Squeaky Clean''\n|Emily\n|Short film\n|-\n|2012\n|''{{sortname|The|Empty Room|nolink=1}}''\n|Juliet\n|Short film\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2013\n|''[[Very Good Girls]]''\n|Eleanor\n|\n|-\n|''We Rise Like Smoke''\n|Young Kyler\n|Short film\n|-\n|2014\n|''{{sortname|The|Edge